President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff as a mark of respect for the victims of the senseless acts of violence that occurred in Boulder, Colorado on March 22, 2021. This order applies to the White House, all public buildings and grounds, military posts, naval stations, naval vessels, and all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad. The flag will be flown at half-staff until sunset on March 27, 2021. This order was signed on March 23, 2021.